<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="68" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pristiphora</taxonomicName>
is the only native genus of 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Nematinae">Nematinae</taxonomicName>
in the Neotropics. Nine species were recorded by Smith (2003), from Mexico to Brazil. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Pristiphora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristiphora fernandezi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezi">Pristiphora fernandezi</taxonomicName>
was described from Colombia, and the specimen from the Podocarpus NP is the first record of both the species and genus from Ecuador.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
